OL,3,CMan banned from keeping dogs following
OL,4,CXL Bully attack
OL,6,FHis dog was later identified as an XL
OL,7,FBully, which is now a banned breed,
OL,8,Fbut was not at the time of the offence.
OL,10,FIlott initially denied that his dog
OL,11,Fhad caused any injury to the victim or
OL,12,Fthe victim's dog, but later pleaded
OL,13,Fguilty in court.
OL,15,FOn Tuesday 2 January, Illot was banned
OL,16,Ffrom keeping dogs for life, handed a
OL,17,Fprison sentence of six months,
OL,18,Fsuspended for 12 months and was
OL,19,Fordered to pay #100 costs to the
OL,20,Fvictim and #187 court costs.
